MemberAdded(address,uint256,bool,string,.details: NewDao events which allows to retrieve important information about DAO on the Dapp (members added end removed, new token and voting Smart Contracts,  snapshot community result, contributions and payment received).

addMember(address,string).details: addMember() function allows the owner to add a new member by their address and name. The function checks if the member is not already in the list, and then adds the new member to the members array, updates the member count, and emits a MemberAdded event.

params.member_: and _name Member address and member name.

constructor.details: NewDao constructor whitch allow to retrieve DAO's choesed name and wallet address of the DAO creator (msg.sender of the createDao() function) to be able to transfert Ownership to the DAO admin.

createToken(string,string).details: CreateToken() function and its getter() are onlyOwner. This function allows the DAO admin to create a token Smart Contract that can mint and distribute tokens to members. These tokens will allow members to participate in DAO's voting sessions.

createVoting().details: createvoting() function and getters() are onlyOwner. This first function will allow DAO admin to create voting Smarts Contracts to organize a vote for any proposal selected by members (proposal selected through a snapshot). TokenAddress is send to the newVoting contract constructor to verify that members are holding a DAO NFT to be able to access voting session.

getDaoName().details: Returns the name of the DAO.

returns._0: A string representing the DAO name.

getMemberByIndex(uint64).details: Returns the DAO member at a given index.

params.index: Index of the member to retrieve.

returns._0: A Member struct containing the member's data.

getMemberCount().details: Returns the total number of DAO members.

returns._0: An integer representing the number of members.

getTokenContract(address).details: This function allows the admin to retrieve a newToken Smart Contract address by index.

getVotingContractByIndex(uint256).details: This function allows the admin to retrieve a newVoting Smart Contract address by index.

getVotingContractCount().details: This function allows the admin to retrieve voting Smart Contract counts by user address.

isMember(address).details: Returns whether an address is a member of the DAO.

params.member_: Address of the member to check.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the address is a member.

makeContribution().details: makeContribution() allows DAO's members to send founds to the DappESSSCIC Smart Contract to pay their contributions.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeMember(address).details: removeMember() function allows the owner to remove a member by their address. The function will replace the member to be removed with the last member in the members array, update the last member's index, and then decrease the member count.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

snapshotResult(string,string,string).details: This function is called by the DAO admin to announce the results of a snapshot and to create a new proposal for voting. The function takes as input a string containing the result of the snapshot and the start and end dates of the voting period. The function increments the proposal ID and creates a new proposal with the given parameters.

params._endDate: The end date of the voting period.
params._startDate: The start date of the voting period.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

_contributions.details: A mapping to store contributions made by members.

_member.details: A mapping to store information about each member of the DAO.

_memberCount.details: Number of members currently in the DAO.

_members.details: An array to store all members of the DAO.

_proposalCount.details: Count of proposals snapshots taken so far.

_proposals.details: A mapping to store information about each proposal.

_tokenAndVotingContracts.details: A mapping to store the token and voting contract addresses for each DAO admin.

_userTokenContracts.details: A mapping to store information about each newToken contract created.

_userVotingContracts.details: A mapping to store information about each newVoting contract created.

createToken(string,string).notice: SCIC must have at least 3 registered members to be able to create a DAO token.

createVoting().notice: SCIC must have at least 3 registered members to be able to create a DAO voting contract.

userdoc.notice: NewDao.sol smart contract allow DAO admin chosen by the SCIC to configure DAO with parameters (members datas and count up to date). Also, on condition that DAO at least count 3 members, admin will be able to deploy two new Smart Contract to manage DAO governance (NewToken.sol and NewVoting.sol). Proposals for voting will be chosen by the community via a snapshot system.
